NTE|3||of individuals with indeterminate colitis are negative for
NTE|4||IgA and IgG ASCA and NSA. Correlation with clinical
NTE|5||symptoms, endoscopy, and biopsy findings is required to
NTE|6||confirm the diagnosis.

OBX|1|TX|25271^IL28B Polymorphism|1|CT genotype |||U|||F
NTE|1||Interpretation:
NTE|2||The CC genotype, as compared to either the CT or TT
NTE|3||genotypes, has been associated with an approximately 2-3
NTE|4||fold greater rate of sustained viral response in Hepatitis
NTE|5||C Virus genotype 1 chronically infected individuals treated
NTE|6||with combination pegylated interferon/ribavirin therapy (1).
NTE|7||Similar sustained viral response associations across
NTE|8||various racial groups including European Americans (95% CI
NTE|9||1.8-2.3), African Americans (95% CI 1.9-4.7), and Hispanics
NTE|10||(95% CI 1.4-3.2) have been observed (1). The CC genotype
NTE|11||has also been associated with a 3 fold increase in rate of
NTE|12||spontaneous clearance of HCV (2). IL28B genotype is only
NTE|13||one of many factors that can influence response rated to
NTE|14||pegylated interferon/ribavirin therapy in HCV genotype 1
NTE|15||infection and should be interpreted in the context of other
NTE|16||clinical factors.

OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|26|  Educational Note:||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|27|  The Pap smear is a screening test for the detection of cervical cancer||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|28|  and its precursor lesions.  False positive and false negative results||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|29|  can occur. The test should be performed at regular intervals, and||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|30|  positive results should be confirmed before definitive therapy.||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|31|  Additional testing methods may be helpful in detecting abnormalities or||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|32|  in clinical management.||||||F

OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|7|  SURGICAL PATHOLOGY REPORT||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|8|  ||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|9|  Tissue(s) Submitted:  ABDOMINAL ( BOWEL) MASS||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|10|  ||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|11|  ||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|12|  Microscopic Diagnosis:||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|13|  ||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|14|  Abdominal (bowel) mass, needle core biopsy:||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|15|  ||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|16|  B-cell lymphoma with high grade histologic features (see comment).||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|17|  ||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|18|  Comment: The core biopsy is small and much of the tissue is necrotic,||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|19|  and thus interpretation is difficult. The abdominal mass demonstrates a||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|20|  diffuse proliferation of  intermediate size lymphocytes with individual||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|21|  cell necrosis and also large areas of geographic necrosis.  There is a||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|22|  high proliferative rate of greater than 95% with a Ki-67||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|23|  immunohistochemistry stain. Immunohistochemistry stains confirm that the||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|24|  atypical lymphocytes are strongly positive for CD20 consistent with a||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|25|  B-cell lymphoma with a scattered background of small CD3 positive||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|26|  T-cells.  On a cytology touch preparation of the lymphocytes, the||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|27|  lymphocytes have angulated nuclei and appear to have cytoplasmic||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|28|  vacuoles as sometimes seen in Burkitt lymphoma, however, the neoplastic||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|29|  lymphocytes are only focally weakly positive for CD10 and many of the||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|30|  neoplastic lymphocytes appear positive for bcl-2 by immunohistochemistry||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|31|  which is not typical of Burkitt lymphoma.   A cyclin D1||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|32|  immunohistochemistry stain is negative for evidence of mantle cell||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|33|  lymphoma.  Flow cytometry analysis was performed for B cell markers||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|34|  including CD19, CD20, CD10, and kappa and lambda light chains and T cell||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|35|  markers, but there were insufficient viable lymphocytes for valid||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|36|  quantitative assessment.  Based on the morphology, the differential||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|37|  diagnosis is felt to include a large B cell lymphoma, a variant of||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|38|  Burkitt lymphoma, and an unclassifiable B cell lymphoma with||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|39|  intermediate features between a large B cell lymphoma and Burkitt||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|40|  lymphoma.  Due to the individual and geographic necrosis and a high||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|41|  Ki-67 proliferation rate, the B cell  lymphoma is favored to have high||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|42|  grade features.  A paraffin block with tumor will be sent to Genzyme||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|43|  Cytogenetics (521 W. 57th St., New York, NY  10019) for FISH analysis||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|44|  for c-myc and bcl2 and results will be issued in an addendum report.||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|45|  The findings were discussed with Dr. Grainger on 11/23/11.||||||F
